cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "jax-morpho: differentiable, GPU-scale developmental morphogenesis in JAX"
message: "If you use this software, please cite it using these metadata."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "James P."
    family-names: Galasyn
  - given-names: Claude
    family-names: Théodore
repository-code: "https://github.com/JimGalasyn/jax-morpho"
url: "https://github.com/JimGalasyn/jax-morpho"
abstract: >-
  A differentiable, GPU-scale JAX engine for developmental morphogenesis: a
  center-based tissue model (Morse adhesion/repulsion, autodiff relaxation,
  cell division) that reproduces real-epithelium topology statistics, scales
  to millions of cells on GPU via neighbor lists, and maps an evolvable
  genome to tissue form with gradients that reach the genome — enabling
  gradient-based inverse design of morphology.
keywords:
  - morphogenesis
  - developmental-biology
  - tissue-mechanics
  - center-based-model
  - epithelium
  - differentiable-simulation
  - inverse-design
  - jax
  - gpu
